{"id":91213,"title":"Cognitive sequelae of traumatic brain injury.","abstract":"Cognitive dysfunction is the leading cause of disability following traumatic brain injury (TBI). This article provides a review of the cognitive sequelae of TBI, with a focus on deficits of executive functioning and everyday thinking skills. The pathophysiology, assessment, and treatment of TBI-related cognitive problems are also discussed. ","date":"2014-02-17","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24529420","annotations":[{"name":"Traumatic brain injury","weight":0.862193,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Traumatic_brain_injury"},{"name":"Pathophysiology","weight":0.790162,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathophysiology"},{"name":"Cognitive dysfunction","weight":0.781843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cognitive_dysfunction"},{"name":"Psychological trauma","weight":0.750806,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychological_trauma"},{"name":"Brain","weight":0.723286,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brain"},{"name":"Disability","weight":0.718103,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disability"},{"name":"Cognition","weight":0.709797,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cognition"},{"name":"Injury","weight":0.697426,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Injury"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.642761,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Acquired brain injury","weight":0.607618,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acquired_brain_injury"},{"name":"Mental disorder","weight":0.575958,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mental_disorder"},{"name":"Sequela","weight":0.567881,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sequela"},{"name":"Executive functioning","weight":0.316891,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Executive_functioning"},{"name":"Psyc